The paper deals with question answering using transformer-based models, which is a common topic in the natural language processing (NLP) community. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the ability of these models to generalize to other domains and with restricted training data, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions experiments on publicly available benchmarks, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
